# Prefer Library Components

When we've adopted a UI library (currently MUI / Material UI), always check its component catalog before building custom elements. Use existing library components and their built-in props/variants rather than reimplementing equivalent functionality with raw HTML or styled primitives.

Examples of MUI components to prefer:
- `LinearProgress` / `CircularProgress` over custom progress bars
- `Alert` / `Snackbar` over custom notification elements
- `Dialog` over custom modals
- `Skeleton` over custom loading placeholders
- `Chip` / `Badge` over custom tag/indicator elements

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — custom progress bar when MUI has one
<Box sx={{ height: 4, bgcolor: 'green', width: `${pct}%`, transition: 'width 1s' }} />

// ✅ GOOD — use MUI LinearProgress
<LinearProgress variant="determinate" value={pct} sx={{ height: 4 }} />
```
